The paper deals with signal processing and optimization in a wireless relay network, which involves topics such as information theory (cs.IT), networking and communication (cs.NI), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), massive MIMO (cs.MM), and computational complexity (cs.COM). The focus on spectral and energy efficiency also suggests a possible fit with the cs.PF sub-category. However, given the emphasis on wireless communication and signal processing, we consider cs.IT and cs.NI to be the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY and cs.MM, and then cs.COM.
